fake_theme <- function(){
  list(
      theme_minimal(),
      scale_fill_manual(values=c('#a6611a','#dfc27d','#f5f5f5','#80cdc1','#018571'), 
                       name="Level of Concern",
                       breaks=c("Extremely concerned", "Very concerned", "Somewhat concerned", "Not very concerned", "Not at all concerned"),
                       labels=c("Extremely concerned", "Very concerned", "Somewhat concerned", "Not very concerned", "Not at all concerned")) 
    )
}
poorJ_theme <- function(){
  list(
      theme_minimal(),
      scale_fill_manual(values=c('#a6611a','#dfc27d','#f5f5f5','#80cdc1','#018571'), 
                       name="Level of Agreement",
                       breaks=c("Strongly disagree", "Tend to disagree", "Neither agree nor disagree", "Tend to agree", "Stronly agree"),
                       labels=c("Strongly disagree", "Tend to disagree", "Neither agree nor disagree", "Tend to agree", "Stronly agree")) 
    )
}
fake_plot <- ggplot(stack_real_fake, aes(segment, percent_new, width=.5, fill = percent_new)) + #reorder(column, by_what)
  geom_bar(aes(fill = concern), stat = "identity", position = "fill") + 
  fake_theme() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(title = "I am concerned about what is real and what is fake on the internet:", x = "Segment", y = "Percent", caption = "Source: Reuters 2018 Digital News Report")
